webpackJsonp([0xf44cdbb076fb],{341:function(e,o){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>So, it\'s the first step in any new development environment: HELLO WORLD! ðŸ™Œ</p>\n<p>Deploying a node.js app on GCP standard environment is actually incredibly easy.</p>\n<h4>Prereq steps:</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>install and initiallize <code>gcloud</code></li>\n<li>login to gcloud</li>\n<li>have billing enabled on your gcloud account ðŸ¤‘</li>\n<li>have a node.js app that runs :)</li>\n<li>enable the <a href="https://console.cloud.google.com/flows/enableapi?apiid=cloudbuild.googleapis.com">Cloud Build API</a></li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Steps to Deploy:</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Create the Project - via the terminal with <code>gcloud app create --project=[PROJECT_ID]</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Go to the node.js code directory or clone the google example: <code>git clone https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/nodejs-docs-samples</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Navigate to the Hello World app: <code>cd nodejs-docs-samples/appengine/hello-world/standard</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Install and Run the app locally: <code>npm install &#x26;&#x26; npm start</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Deploy the app! - from the same root directory of the app, run: <code>gcloud app deploy</code> then follow the prompts to select region, etc.\n<img src="static/images/gcloud-deploy.png" alt="gcloud-deploy"></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>View the app once it finished deploying: <code>gcloud app browse</code>\n<img src="static/images/gcloud-app-browse.png" alt="gcloud-app-browse"></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<div class="note">\n  <strong>Note:</strong> The default location for a deployment is: <pre>https://PROJECT_ID.REGION_ID.r.appspot.com</pre> Alternatively, you can use: <pre>gcloud app browse</pre> to have the page open for you.\n</div>\n<p>And you are done! Yes, it was actually that easy. Now, lets look into some additional features/capabilities of GCP + Node.js, like <a href="../gcp-datastore/">GCP Datastore</a>.</p>',frontmatter:{date:"June 02, 2021",path:"/gcp-nodejs-hello-world",title:"node.js on GCP"}}},pathContext:{}}}});
